USER IMPACT:
The color contrast between text and background makes it difficult for users with visual impairments, including those who are legally blind or have low vision, to read the text on this page. This can cause eye strain and may prevent users from accessing important information.

REMEDIATION PLAN:
[{'step': 1, 'action': "Inspect the CSS style property 'color' and the background color of the element", 'code': '<p style='}, {'step': 2, 'action': "Check the color contrast using a tool like WebAIM's Color Contrast Checker or a Color Contrast Checker browser extension", 'code': ''}, {'step': 3, 'action': 'Use the hex code #888 for the text color, which has a low contrast with the background', 'code': 'color: #333;', 'replace': 'color: #888;'}, {'step': 4, 'action': "Replace the #333 hex code for the button's text color which currently has low contrast", 'code': 'color: #fff;', 'replace': 'color: #fff;'}, {'step': 5, 'action': 'Apply the required background and text color values in the CSS styles for the elements to achieve sufficient color contrast.', 'code': '/* For the button */
.et_pb_button {
  background-color: #333;
  color: #fff;
}
/* For the paragraphs */
.et_pb_column {
  color: #333
};'}]
